# ── Phase 0 data pipeline ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per CLAUDE.md §4: staging is raw downloads, never committed. Cleaned
# accepted parquet is large + reproducible. DB files are gitignored.
# `rejected/` IS committed — it documents data quality issues over time.
data/staging/
data/cleaned/*/all.parquet
data/cleaned/*/accepted/
data/cleaned/*/rejected_pydantic.jsonl
data/exports/
data/db/
!data/cleaned/*/rejected/
!data/cleaned/*/rejected/reasons.jsonl
!data/cleaned/*/rejected/all.parquet

# Kaggle credentials should never be committed.
*.kaggle.json
kaggle.json
.kaggle/

